@page
@* @model SlippiStatsWeb.Pages.FAQModel *@
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "FAQ";
}

<div class="text-center" style="max-width: 800px; margin: auto;">
    <h1 class="subheader">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

    <h3>What is FramePeak?</h3>
    <p>A free tool for analyzing your Super Smash Bros. Melee gameplay using .SLP files recorded through Slippi.</p>

    <h3>What file types can I upload?</h3>
    <p>Currently, only .SLP files are supported. These are generated when you play Melee using Slippi.</p>

    <h3>How long until my stats appear?</h3>
    <p>Stats are available immediately after upload. You can view them under “View My Slippi Data.”</p>

    <h3>What do I do if my stats look wrong?</h3>
    <p>Double-check that you uploaded the correct file. If something still seems off, submit a bug report through our <a asp-page="/Feedback">Feedback</a> page.</p>

    <h3>Do I need to create an account?</h3>
    <p>Yes. Creating an account allows us to store your stats and improve the accuracy of your analysis.</p>

    <h3>How do you handle my data?</h3>
    <p>Your replay files are stored temporarily for parsing and then deleted. Only parsed stats remain in our database.</p>
</div>
